The paper discusses a framework for estimating the position of a vehicle using map information and measurements of speed, which is relevant to the fields of computer security (cs.CR) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the sensitivity and commercial value of data collected in insurance telematics programs, which falls under the category of social and information sciences (cs.SI). The use of speed limits and trajectory information suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the field of information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper mentions performance evaluations, which may involve computer vision techniques (cs.CV).
